      • areEquivalentEquations

        int areEquivalentEquations(String respEqn,
                           String solvedEqnsStr,
                           String constants)
                    throws ProcessExecutionException,
                           EquationFormatException
        Determines whether two equations are equivalent. We assume that the left side of each equation in solvedEqnsStr is the same single variable.
        Parameters:
        respEqn - an equation
        solvedEqnsStr - comma-separated equations solved for the same single variable
        constants - the given constants
        Returns:
        the number of the matching author's equation if the equations are equivalent
        Throws:
        ProcessExecutionException - if the process can't be executed properly
        EquationFormatException - if the result is not a reduced equation

      • areEquivalentExpressions

        int areEquivalentExpressions(String exprn1,
                             String exprn2,
                             String constants)
                      throws ProcessExecutionException,
                             EquationFormatException
        Determines whether two expressions (not equations) are equivalent.
        Parameters:
        exprn1 - one expression or equation
        exprn2 - the other expression or equation
        constants - the given constants
        Returns:
        1 if the expressions are equivalent, 0 otherwise
        Throws:
        ProcessExecutionException - if the process can't be executed properly
        EquationFormatException - if the result is not a reduced expression
